cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with machine learning on graphs and networks with applications ranging from vehicular network design to IoT traffic management to social network recommendations. It also focuses on representation learning for heterogeneous networks, which is a common problem in social and information networks. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with supervised machine learning tasks and representation learning using deep learning. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) is another possible sub-category as the paper proposes a novel algorithm for node representation learning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with machine learning and deep learning techniques. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for exploring higher order neighborhoods in networks.
